					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Collision detection is very hard to wrap your mind around in the beginning, so the more you can simplify it, the better. I haven't read the article to comprehend it in great detail, but it seems to be pretty short and sweet. If not done correctly, collision code can be littered with messy comparisons and off-by-one errors. I know when I started, I had lots of problems with being off by one. If an object is 16x16 pixels in size, the corners are actually at 0,0 and 15,15; not 0,0 and 16,16. If you code this wrong, the object will not fit between 2 16x16 pixel solid objects <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />.</div>

